{
  "texts": [
    "Note that we distinguish between the generating model (the LLM that generated the AIGT) and the measurement model (the LLM that provides the word probability estimates, where needed).",
    "The word 'model' could also refer to a detection model; for clarity, we refer to such a model as a detector.",
    "Studies have indicated that human annotators can no longer reliably distinguish between AIGT and human-written text (Liu et al., 2024; Sarvazyan et al., 2023).",
    "However, our data differs from the data used in those studies in two important respects:",
    "(1) it is social media-style text, rather than academic writing, news, or reviews, and (2) we consider text from fine-tuned LLMs, and there is a chance that the fine-tuning process might introduce some artifacts that make the resulting text more identifiable to human readers, regardless of the performance of the detection algorithms."
  ]
}